{"type":"text","timestamp":1773352050159,"sessionID":"ses_31c0172a9ffeekk99N9QZhhvnC","part":{"id":"prt_ce4048abb0014uEL7i7eef2aeX","sessionID":"ses_31c0172a9ffeekk99N9QZhhvnC","messageID":"msg_ce4047e7a001Tcvqtc29CFn3NP","type":"text","text":"Both typecheck and build pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n### Subtask 1: TOON Format Specification & Formatter Module\n**New file: `src/lib/toon.ts`** — Complete TOON format specification and encoding functions:\n- **Status codes**: BL=backlog, PL=planned, IP=in_progress, BK=blocked, IR=in_review, DN=done, XX=cancelled\n- **Priority codes**: C=critical, H=high, M=medium, L=low, W=wishlist\n- **Difficulty codes**: T=trivial, E=easy, M=medium, H=hard, V=very_hard\n- **Agent status codes**: QU=queued, IN=installing, RU=running, CO=completed, VF=verified, FA=failed, MG=merged, RT=retry, RC=resolving_conflict\n- **Pipe-delimited fields**, comma-separated lists within fields, `>` prefix for subtask nesting\n- Encoding functions for all data types: features, subtasks, wave status, verification, check results, archive results, command schemas\n- Self-describing legend via `toonLegend()` for `woco describe --output toon`\n\n### Subtask 2: Updated Output Infrastructure\n**Modified: `src/lib/output.ts`**:\n- `OutputFormat` type now includes `\"toon\"` as third option\n- `resolveOutputFormat()` recognizes `toon` from `--output`, `WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon`, and auto-detects via `WOMBO_AGENT=1`\n- `output()` accepts optional 4th `toonRenderer` callback\n- `outputError()` and `outputMessage()` emit TOON format (ERR|msg, MSG|msg)\n\n### Subtask 3: Wired TOON into All Commands\n- **features list** → compact `#FL|count|effort` header + pipe-delimited feature rows\n- **features show** → `#FS` detail view with subtasks, deps, constraints, notes\n- **features add** → `ADD|id|priority|difficulty|effort|title` result\n- **features set-status** → `SET|id|old|new|changed` result\n- **features graph** → `GRAPH|nodes|edges|orphans` + mermaid source\n- **describe** → TOON legend when `--output toon` with no command; compact schema for specific commands\n- **Schema registry** updated to advertise `toon` in `--output` enum\n- **Help text** updated with toon format documentation and `WOMBO_AGENT`/`WOMBO_OUTPUT` env vars\n\n### Constraint Compliance\n- ✅ Third format alongside text and json (`--output toon`)\n- ✅ 60%+ token reduction vs JSON (e.g., `cli-bugs|BL|H|M|PT2H|0|Fix CLI bugs` vs `{\"id\":\"cli-bugs\",\"status\":\"backlog\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\",\"effort\":\"PT2H\",\"completion\":0,\"title\":\"Fix CLI bugs\",\"depends_on\":[]}`)\n- ✅ Consistent key abbreviations across all commands\n- ✅ Self-describing legend via `woco describe --output toon`\n- ✅ Pipe-delimited fields, single/two-char status codes, abbreviated enums\n- ✅ Auto-detect agent context via `WOMBO_AGENT=1` env var\n- ✅ Parseable — agents can reliably split on `|` delimiter\n- ✅ Unambiguous abbreviations (no conflicts between priority M=medium and difficulty M=medium — they're in different positional fields)","time":{"start":1773352050157,"end":1773352050157}}}
